FBIS4-7823 "dreeu067_i_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-067 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Battle for Gorazde Continuing Battle for Gorazde Continuing Civilian Areas Shelled AU0604144694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 6 Apr 94 AU0604144694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Report by Enes Murtovic from Gorazde] [Text] The siren sounding general danger (?shows) that there is no peace in Gorazde again today. The chetniks [words indistinct] are shelling civilian areas and the defense lines. The highest caliber shells are again destroying the Gorazde region that borders Foca, Cajnice, and Rogatica. In the course of the day, several howitzer shells landed on the town. Even though the residents of Gorazde are in shelters all the time, the casualty figures are nevertheless [passage indistinct] (?41) women and old men. [words indistinct] arrival of General Michael Rose, commander of the UN forces in Bosnia-Herzegovina, separated the chetniks from their (?deadly) weapons for only a moment. As we send this report, explosions are once again being heard in the town's suburbs. The chetniks are also attacking the town itself. The [word indistinct] and the suffering of the population in the protected zone of Gorazde is continuing before the eyes of the international community, which again is not taking [word indistinct] measures to stop the latest offensive by the chetniks. This is Enes Murtovic reporting for Radio and Television Bosnia- Herzegovina from the Press Center of the Gorazde region.
